Java Interview Points (Freshers)
1. What is Java?

Java is a high-level, object-oriented, platform-independent programming language developed by Oracle Corporation.

2. Why is Java Platform Independent?

Java source code is compiled into bytecode, which runs on the Java Virtual Machine (JVM). Therefore, the same program can run on different operating systems.

3. Difference Between JDK, JRE, and JVM
Term	Meaning
JVM	Executes Java bytecode
JRE	JVM + Libraries required to run Java programs
JDK	JRE + Development tools (compiler, debugger)
